Question 1: Simulate the Dataset
First, let's create a dataset with ğ‘‹1 and ğ‘‹2following a bivariate normal distribution with zero mean, variance 1, and correlation ğœŒ.
# Load the MASS library for generating multivariate normal data
library(MASS)

# Set parameters
n <- 1000            # Number of observations
rho <- 0.7           # Correlation coefficient
mu <- c(0, 0)        # Mean vector
sigma <- matrix(c(1, rho, rho, 1), nrow = 2)  # Covariance matrix

# Simulate the bivariate normal data
set.seed(123)  # For reproducibility
data <- mvrnorm(n, mu, sigma)
X1 <- data[, 1]
X2 <- data[, 2]

# Display the first few rows of the dataset
head(data)
